            <q>not raised charges of any of them"?</q>
            Secondly, why does Mr. Tucker want me to send my evidence to him if he is not doing that? What is there to investigate on Irwin Mitchell's behalf if it is not doing anything about conditional fee or success fee agreements?</p><p>
            With all my good will, especially to my hon. Friend the Minister, who has been great in bringing the matter to the forefront and putting it in the newspapers&#x2014;I am sure all hon. Members appreciate how the work load has risen in the past few months in relation to what he and those who work in our offices do&#x2014;I must tell the Law
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_260wh' title='Col. 260WH &mdash; HC Deb 03 March 2004 vol 418 c260WH' name='column_260wh' href='#column_260wh' rel='bookmark'>260WH</a>
            Society, which I assume will read this debate, that I raised the subject four years ago this month and it should have investigated it further. It knew what was happening in 1999 but did nothing. I am pleased that it is doing something now, but, further to the comments of my hon. Friend the Member for Barnsley, West and Penistone, I would be happier if the Law Society, on learning of solicitors who have asked for money&#x2014;whether or not they took it, as in the case that I highlighted&#x2014;would go into their offices, review the cases and ensure that moneys that were wrongly stopped are paid. We must not forget that at least 50 per cent. of the cases are posthumous.
          </p>
